<br>
Malo is better than Mala.  I can't imagine how you think 1 spell makes mages one of the best debuffers in the game.<br>
<br>
Entire guild raids can crash to a halt if the last shaman logs off.  This is rarely the case for mages -- and when it is, it's because of COTH, not debuffs.<br>
<br>
I also dispute that necros ever outdamaged us.  I remember, Back In The Day, playing my warrior and the guild mage would break the froglok lord room using her FS'd earth pet.  Between the pet's damage output, fireshield and massive hit points... well, no necro was going to do that.  Their charm is cool when they solo and can feign, but it's not so cool when the charm is resisted, they feign and the rest of the party is thinking &quot;ohshit&quot;.<br>
<br>
Mages were the mack daddy before Kunark.  I used to get really pissed about how much better a mage pet was at tanking AND doing damage than my warrior was capable of.  (We broke the Lord spawn by sending in the pet and letting it tank all 3 mobs to weaken them and build agro -- we were short on enchanters, but when the mage was around it didn't matter.  I watched the pet and knew if I tried the same stunt with my decked out level 50 warrior, we would have all died.)  These days, of course, mages are scoffed at, their pets are frequently more harmful than good, and even when they're running perfectly they're 4th rate damage dealers or worse.  Show me a mob that can only be hit with Lure and I'll show you a mage sitting on his butt watching TV.<br>
<br>
I think most of the upset mages are people who played or played with old school pre-Kunark mages.<br>
<br>
You may think your abilities are keen in some ways now, but for old schoolers, it's been like watching your classic '57 Chevy rust in the driveway because the landlord refuses the fix the garage roof.  It's still a classic '57 Chevy, but it used to be a whole lot better.<br>
<br>
